npc/damar: You made it through Stage 2. But this is a different place entirely.
npc/damar: Stage 2 was the surface web. This is what runs underneath it — the Cyber Network, where the money actually moves.
npc/damar: Every server, every data pipe, every gambling transaction at 3 AM — it all passes through this layer.
npc/damar: And this is where losing turns into something worse than losing. This is where the debt begins.
npc/damar: When a player runs dry, the platform offers a loan — "pinjol," online credit, one tap away. Small at first. The interest compounds daily.
npc/damar: Miss a payment and it doubles. Borrow again to cover it and it doubles faster. The debt is not an accident of gambling — the debt is the product.
npc/damar: I know that tide. I took one loan to cover one loss. The interest doubled while I slept. I borrowed again to pay it, and the number only ever went up — never down, not once.
npc/damar: I lost the shop. Then the savings. Then the house my parents left me. All of it, to a balance on a screen that never stopped growing.
npc/damar: The creatures here are Firewall Sentinels — built to stop people like you from tracing the signal. They do not reason. They do not negotiate.
npc/damar: And watch beneath your feet. In this layer, the debt rises.
npc/damar: A tide of red climbs the longer you linger — the system compounding what you owe, second by second, whether you play or not. Stand still and it swallows you. You have to keep climbing.
npc/damar: You cannot outspend it. You can only climb out. Move.
